# Fix Supabase Initialization Crash

The application is crashing on startup with `Uncaught Error: supabaseKey is required`. This is caused by [src/lib/supabase.ts](file:///c:/Users/%D0%90%D0%B4%D0%BC%D0%B8%D0%BD%D0%B8%D1%81%D1%82%D1%80%D0%B0%D1%82%D0%BE%D1%80/Downloads/speedy-gadgets-hub-main%20%281%29/speedy-gadgets-hub-main/src/lib/supabase.ts) attempting to initialize `supabaseAdmin` using `VITE_SUPABASE_SECRET_KEY`, which is missing from the [.env](file:///c:/Users/%D0%90%D0%B4%D0%BC%D0%B8%D0%BD%D0%B8%D1%81%D1%82%D1%80%D0%B0%D1%82%D0%BE%D1%80/Downloads/speedy-gadgets-hub-main%20%281%29/speedy-gadgets-hub-main/.env) file.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> `VITE_SUPABASE_SECRET_KEY` (Supabase service_role key) is required for AI features to work. However, exposing this key via the `VITE_` prefix makes it accessible to the client-side browser, which is a security risk.
> I will implement a fix to prevent the crash when the key is missing, but for the AI features to work, you will still need to provide a key or refactor how secrets are handled.

## Proposed Changes

### Supabase Integration

#### [MODIFY] [supabase.ts](file:///c:/Users/Администратор/Downloads/speedy-gadgets-hub-main%20(1)/speedy-gadgets-hub-main/src/lib/supabase.ts)
- Update `supabaseAdmin` initialization to be optional. If `VITE_SUPABASE_SECRET_KEY` is missing, `supabaseAdmin` will be `null` instead of throwing an error.
- Add descriptive error logging when the key is missing.

#### [MODIFY] [groq.ts](file:///c:/Users/Администратор/Downloads/speedy-gadgets-hub-main%20(1)/speedy-gadgets-hub-main/src/lib/groq.ts)
- Add checks for `supabaseAdmin` being `null` before calling `functions.invoke`.
- Throw a clear user-facing error if an attempt is made to use AI features without the required configuration.

### Edge Function Auth (401 Error Fix)

#### [MODIFY] [config.toml](file:///c:/Users/Администратор/Downloads/speedy-gadgets-hub-main%20(1)/speedy-gadgets-hub-main/supabase/config.toml)
- [x] Corrected `project_id` to `xbuyuflvmfauvdlpguem`.

#### [DEBUG] Manual Steps for User
- Check the Supabase Dashboard -> Edge Functions -> `telegram-bot` -> Settings.
- Ensure "Verify JWT" (or "Authentication") is turned **OFF**.
- If the above doesn't work, try updating the Telegram webhook URL to include the apikey:
  `https://xbuyuflvmfauvdlpguem.supabase.co/functions/v1/telegram-bot?apikey=YOUR_ANON_KEY`

